What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Enterprise Mobility Management Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Enterprise Mobility Management Market

The enterprise mobility management market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 24.85% in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research report on enterprise mobility management market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in the demand from various industry verticals is escalating the growth of enterprise mobility management market.

Enterprise mobility management (EMM) refers to a set of technology, processes and people that are working towards managing increased array of wireless networks, smart devices and related services. The technology explores the opportunities of mobile computing within the various businesses. EMM assists businesses in managing securely any mobile device to improve employee satisfaction and productivity.

The proliferation of new mobile devices across various industries acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of enterprise mobility management market. The adoption of BYOD initiatives to improve worker productivity, allowing employees to work from anywhere, at any time, and rise in real-time data access and penetration of cloud-based EMM services among SMEs accelerate the market growth. The increase in trend of work from home due to the COVID-19 pandemic drives the adoption of EMM solutions and increase in popularity of the technology owning to the increased data accuracy and device sharing, enhanced employee productivity further influence the market. Additionally, high penetration of smartphones, demand for user-friendly and feature-packed software, rapid digitization and high adoption of the technology because of its ability to create a cohesive ecosystem positively affect the enterprise mobility management market. Furthermore, rise in number of cyber-attacks on personal devices and business-critical data extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029.

On the other hand, issues with EMM solutions catering to every business need for a consistent end-user experience are expected to obstruct the market. Poor enterprise system integrators and data security and privacy concerns are projected to challenge the enterprise mobility management market in the forecast period of 2022-2029.

